OL,6,FAfter three years, it went live and it
OL,7,Fhurtled into the stratosphere. The    
OL,8,Fextra energy, interactivity and       
OL,9,Funpredictability made the show        
OL,10,Fcompulsive.                           
OL,12,FAs I said, it was rare for the BBC to 
OL,13,Fshow such commitment to a show that was
OL,14,Fsimply TV candyfloss  and that is not
OL,15,Fmeant as a criticism of NHP.          
OL,17,FArguably, the soaring ratings planted 
OL,18,Fsome of the seeds for the show's later
OL,19,Fdifficulties.                         
OL,3,CWould more live programming revive the
OL,4,Cfortunes of linear TV?                
OL,22,                                  G7/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
