OL,6,FThe BBC normally argues that ratings  
OL,7,Falone are not the best way to judge a 
OL,8,Fprogramme's success. However this     
OL,9,Fargument has always tended to go out  
OL,10,Fthe window as soon as it found a      
OL,11,Fprogramme capable of matching or      
OL,12,Fbeating ITV.                          
OL,14,FOnce ratings started falling  as was 
OL,15,Finevitable  increasingly desperate   
OL,16,Fefforts were made to try to get the   
OL,17,Fratings up. These coincided with      
OL,18,Fattempts to balance budget cuts.      
OL,3,CWould more live programming revive the
OL,4,Cfortunes of linear TV?                
OL,22,                                  G8/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35009
